UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2510
1 participating in outside sports and reading political memoirs; and
2 WHEREAS, Bob Quick has contributed to the economic vitality and overall quality
3 of life in Lexington and the surrounding region; and
4 WHEREAS, Bob Quick is offered sincere commendation and gratitude for his years
5 of exemplary service and is extended best wishes for future success and good fortune as
6 he embarks upon a well-earned retirement;
7 NOW, THEREFORE,
8 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
9 Kentucky:
10 Section 1. The members of the Senate recognize Bob Quick's legacy for his
11 contributions to the economic vitality and his commitment to bettering Commerce
12 Lexington and the surrounding region.
13 Section 2. The members of the Senate honor Bob Quick upon his forthcoming
14 retirement as president and CEO of Lexington Commerce on July 31, 2026, and wish him
15 and his family well.
16 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
17 Resolution to Senator Reginald L. Thomas for delivery.
